<br>
This posts intention was to share my experiences with others, on a board that's shown negativity toward our stereotypical &quot;said&quot; role of being nothing but a &quot;rod whore&quot;.  <br>
It wasn't my <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>intention</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> brag</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> about my abilities, or to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> scoff</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at other VT able mages -  I'm here to give my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> feedback</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, to all that wish to read of it, of a days clearing in Vex Thal  <br>
<br>
I did not tailor this post for any specific person, level, or ability.  With that said, I have spoken of my experiences, and maybe down the line others can <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> relate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to what and give them a good feeling to share with others. It may inspire a lower level mage-reader of this board to aspire to be something <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> more</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than what a portion of this board claims we're only useful for: coth and mod rods.<br>
<br>
I for one disliked this board a year ago, and up until recently I've realized while I don't agree with the broad majority of the negative opinions held here by some, I do agree that this is a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>fantastic</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> source for information, for all levels.<br>
